snippet.textDisplay: Loving this series. Great acting, very moving scenes, very real characters. So many "follow me" scenes have brought me to tears especially Simon Peter hauling in his load of fish and Jesus healing the paralytic and leper. Plus the wine miracle at the wedding. This episode in particular was interesting and fascinating with the disciples and Mary discussing how they first met Jesus, how He called them and how strange and wondrous it now was to follow Him. Coz that's what I bet they woulda done in real life. And I absolutely love Matthew! Fantastic acting - he's so odd and curious and funny but again, so real. Thanks Dallas and VidAngel :)

snippet.textDisplay:
Oh my. The scene between Jesus and Nicodemus, where he realises he is standing on Holy ground and Jesus embraces him, brought out a cry from deep within my soul, where I just couldn't stop thinking about Jesus' embrace in my life, and I just couldn't stop crying. Even now, remembering just a few seconds of that scene sets me off again in emoticons and tears. I'm so grateful for the prence of God in that moment, as it spoke to me with such a depth that I've not experienced before. I was a complete mess, went to bed still in tears, changed. And then knowing the girl played the cello for that scene made it even more pure.
I've been sharing The Chosen with my church and I pray that many more come to intimately experience Jesus' love for us ❤️

snippet.textDisplay: I can honestly say, speaking for myself.. that I had a walk with the Lord, drifted and returned. But it still wasn't the same as when I first believed, but it was.. ok?  However.. one thing about this crisis has caused me to re dedicate as it were, my life back again.  What was interesting was I had been praying for that fire to return.  The fire that I once had.. and this was before my mother went home Feb 26th this year.  Well, when this fully hit at first I was afraid as I think most were.. but I decided to have prayer time and a Bible study again and my roomate.. God bless him for putting up with me, agreed with me.  Time to get serious with Jesus all over again.  Today has been a blessed day, and just so you know it's been one thing after another with me since mom went home.. I had a horrible cold after mom's funeral, then after I got over that several days later I got a sinus infection.. then after that (today) I woke up with the gout.  Something I haven't had trouble me in some time,  and it's not bothering me in the sense that my fire has returned..He gave it back.. and what I do now on twitter has really grown.. with a lot of follows and likes.. something I've not had before.. and I know it's all because of the Lord. It's all about Him. God bless you all for what you are doing, it's powerful!  Last point.. I do know one of your extra's.. he is a Pharisee and that particular Pharisee is Steve Shermett.  He was my Rabbi (Yes I'm Jewish) when I first moved back to Tucson AZ to be close to my young son again after my wife and  I divorced.  Another long story but.. again.. In Jesus Name, May the Lord bless you all for such an amazing gift.. and tool to encourage and reach the lost.  Chen v' Shalom b' shem Y'S'hu-a!

snippet.textDisplay:
I love Nicodemas, Eric Avari!.. Such a wonderful actor!!.. How I wish we could see more of him.. The roof top meeting with Jesus was so awesome.. I wish it was longer!..

You can feel the heaviness on Nicodemas as the time to make a decision to leave and follow Christ or choose his role with the sanhedrin and leave with his family drew closer and closer.. He was so torn.. But the anguish behind the wall as he cried was so palpable.. I CRY every time!!.. My heart breaks for him..

But atleast he found the truth and got to see and speak with the Messiah, something I'm sure he thought he would of never see much less experience first hand.. Thank you Eric Avari for bringing Nicodemas to life for us!.. ❤

The bronze serpent on the pole has long been understood as a sort of prophecy of the crucifixion-- just as those who looked at the bronze serpent were cured of their snakebites, those who look upon Christ and his sacrifice on the cross are cured of their sins.

Really neat to see how the OT stories paved the way for the gospel.

snippet.textDisplay:
Read the Bible. Start in the Book of John then read Ephesians and Galatians. Then the Book of Revelation. We are in the end of times. Accept Jesus as your savior for ALL of your sins, past, present, and future. Jesus' blood paid for them all.
For it is by grace you have been saved, through faith—and this is not from yourselves, it is the gift of God— not by works, so that no one can boast. Ephesians 2:8-9.
If you confess with your mouth the Lord Jesus and believe in your heart that God has raised Him from the dead, you will be saved. Romans 10:9
Salvation is found in no one else, for there is no other name under heaven given to mankind by which we must be saved. Acts 4:12
Receive Jesus as your Lord and savior while there is still time. Time is running out.
